Luca, I've reviewed the registration template. The HTML structure is solid -- good accessibility (aria-describedby, aria-invalid, aria-live regions, autocomplete attributes, proper labels). Heydon would approve. But there are some design issues:

**Issue 1: No component CSS.**
The template uses class names (`.form-field`, `.field-error`, `.field-hint`, `.form-error-banner`) but the components layer in main.css is still empty. These classes don't style anything yet. We need the component CSS added.

**Issue 2: Class names don't match my spec.**
I specified `.auth-form`, `.auth-form__group`, `.auth-form__error`, etc. The template uses `.form-field`, `.field-error`, `.field-hint`. Either the CSS matches the template or the template matches the spec -- we just need consistency. I'm fine with the more generic names (.form-field, .field-error, .field-hint) since they'll be reused for the login form too. Let's go with those.

**Issue 3: Missing form wrapper.**
The `<form>` needs a wrapper (or the form itself needs a class) that sets `max-inline-size: 24rem` and `margin-inline: auto`. Right now the form will stretch to the full container width (40rem). That's too wide for a three-field auth form. It should be narrower and centered.

**Issue 4: Missing spacing structure.**
The form needs vertical rhythm between fields. The `.form-field` groups need `gap` or margin to create the `--space-lg` (24px) separation I specified. Without it, everything will be crammed together.

**Issue 5: Footer text styling.**
The "Already have an account? Sign in" line at the bottom needs to be centered, muted color, smaller font. Right now it's just a bare `<p>` with no class.

**Issue 6: Heading text.**
The template says "Create an account" but I specified "Create your account." Small thing, but "your" makes it feel more personal and directed.

Here's what I'd suggest for the component CSS (Lea can add this to the components layer):

```css
@layer components {
  /* Auth form -- registration, login */
  form[action="/register"],
  form[action="/login"] {
    max-inline-size: 24rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .form-field {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .field-hint {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
  }

  .field-error {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-danger);
  }

  .form-error-banner {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-danger);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--color-danger-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
}
```

And the footer paragraph needs a class. Can you update the template to add something like `class="auth-footer"` to the "Already have an account?" paragraph?

These are refinements, not blockers. The functionality is correct. But the visual output matters -- it's a user's first impression.

